election_record.label: New York 1805 State Senate, Western District

overview.note: Nicholas Lock and Nathaniel Nichols are amalgamations of two candidates.
The town and county totals listed here add up to 10432 votes for Nathaniel Locke in the Western District. The official canvass of votes, however, list 10443 votes for Locke.

sub_unit.name: Cayuga
sub_unit.note: Nathaniel Locke received 1 vote as Nathan Locke.

sub_unit.name: Aurelius
sub_unit.note: John Nicholas received 1 vote as John Nicholson.
Nathaniel Nicholas received 1 vote as Nathaniel Nicholson.

sub_unit.name: Owasco
sub_unit.note: Votes from Owasco were not included in the official canvass of votes.

sub_unit.name: Genesee
sub_unit.note: The town votes listed here add up to 391 votes for Nathaniel Locke in Genesee County. The official canvass of votes, however, lists 401 votes for Locke.
In 1802, Genesee county was formed from part Ontario county, but the two continued to vote together in 1805, and most newspapers list returns from both counties together.
